# Focus theming

Read [`docs/FOCUS_THEMING.md`](../../docs/FOCUS_THEMING.md) before editing focus styles or interactive chrome.

## Rules

1. **Theme tokens, not hex** — use `--labs-control-focus-ring`, `--labs-control-focus-ring-inset`, or family `--*-focus-ring`. Map `--theme-focus-ring` once on app shell.
2. **Outset vs inset** — toolbar / split controls → outset; popover toggles / dense panels → inset. Do not stack both on one control.
3. **Never clip rings** — no `overflow: hidden` on split shells or settings popovers; use `.labs-focus-ring-host` + `--labs-focus-ring-bleed` on sticky bars.
4. **No bare `outline: none`** — always add `:focus-visible` replacement (shared utility or component token).
5. **Portaled UI** — duplicate focus + brand tokens on portal root class (dropdown paper, metronome appearance wrapper), not `:root`.

## Checklist

- [ ] Ring mode chosen (outset / inset / shell `:focus-within`)
- [ ] App shell or portal class maps `--theme-focus-ring`
- [ ] Keyboard tab shows visible, unclipped ring
- [ ] Sticky toolbar has bleed padding if it contains icon/split controls

Menu open/close patterns: [`docs/A11Y_MENU_PATTERNS.md`](../../docs/A11Y_MENU_PATTERNS.md).
